HEADWORD: Pewfellow
<hw>Pew"fel`low</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who occupies the same pew with another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An intimate associate; a companion.</def>
